commit.message:
do not hardcode python executable name and use sys.executable

Python executabe name should not be hardcoded.
Use instead sys.executable().

Signed-off-by: Tomasz Kłoczko <kloczek@github.com>
Actually, just bail out on almost any error.
Ignore broken pipes in the worker.
Refactor stuff and add a file buffering mode for processes. Drop py2 support.
Handle bytes the same way in ThreadedBufferingBase.
Fix regression caused by the ``universal_newlines`` (now the internals don't decode strings).
Set universal new lines by default (line buffering doesn't work properly without it).
Don't use close_fds on windows (it's disallowed with stdout/err redirection).
Add attributes to disable pytest collecting the instances.
